# Project Structure Guidelines

## Key Files
- [src/App.js](mdc:src/App.js) - Main application component
- [src/index.js](mdc:src/index.js) - Application entry point
- [AuthContext.js](mdc:src/context/AuthContext.js) - Context management setup
- [src/services/api.js](mdc:src/services/api.js) - API configuration
- [roles.js](mdc:src/constants/roles.js) - define role constant in application

## Best Practices
1. Keep components small and focused on a single responsibility
2. Use feature-based organization for complex features
3. Maintain clear separation between UI components and business logic
4. Follow consistent naming conventions:
   - Components: PascalCase (e.g., `OrderForm.js`)
   - Utilities: camelCase (e.g., `formatPrice.js`)
   - Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
